# Solidaris — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

NX Monorepo with two Angular apps (`iSHARE`, `iCRM`) sharing a single source of truth for components, styles, routes, and utilities.

- **Monorepo**: NX
- **Framework**: Angular latest
- **Component Library**: PrimeNG latest
- **Design System**: Plectrum — https://plectrum.solidaris.be/5cba76f64/p/8028d1-plectrum-design-system
- **Figma UI Kit**: https://www.figma.com/design/YNZ1DlSjDNUXrvkxlSp10D/Plectrum-for-PrimeNG--Main-?node-id=6961-92390 (SSOT for all visual decisions)
- **SCSS Architecture**: ITCSS (01-settings → 07-utilities)
- **CSS Naming**: BEMIT (Block__Element--Modifier)
- **Component Docs**: Storybook (global, shared)

---

## MCP Servers

| Server | Purpose | URL |
|---|---|---|
| Figma | Inspect Plectrum UI Kit, extract tokens and specs | `http://127.0.0.1:3845/mcp` |
| PrimeNG | Query PrimeNG component API, props and examples | `https://primeng.org/mcp` |

**Always query these MCP servers before implementing any component:**
1. Use **Figma MCP** to inspect the node in the Plectrum UI Kit and extract exact design tokens, spacing, colors, and typography
2. Use **PrimeNG MCP** to confirm which PrimeNG component to use and its available props/variants
3. Only write custom code when both MCPs confirm no existing solution covers the requirement

