## Workspace Structure

```
solidaris-nx/
├── apps/
│   ├── ishare/        # iSHARE app — no shared logic here
│   └── icrm/          # iCRM app — no shared logic here
├── libs/
│   ├── ui/            # SSOT — all shared Angular components
│   ├── styles/        # SSOT — all SCSS/ITCSS tokens and utilities
│   └── plectrum/      # SSOT — design system integration
├── storybook/         # Global Storybook for all libs/ui components
└── tools/generators/  # NX component scaffolding
```

---

## ITCSS Structure (`libs/styles/src/`)

```
01-settings/   — _colors.scss, _tokens.scss, _variables.scss
02-tools/      — _mixins.scss, _functions.scss
03-generic/    — _reset.scss
04-elements/   — _typography.scss, _links.scss
05-objects/    — _layout.scss          (prefix: o-)
06-components/ — per-component files   (prefix: c-)
07-utilities/  — _utilities.scss       (prefix: u-)
```

Every SCSS change must land in the correct ITCSS layer. Never write styles outside `libs/styles`.

---

## Rules

### Rule — Quality Over Speed
- Take the correct architectural path, never the shortcut
- Prefer clean, debt-free solutions over quick fixes
- Avoid wrappers, shims, or indirection unless truly necessary
- Leave the codebase better than you found it

### Rule — Single Source of Truth (SSOT)
- All shared components → `libs/ui` (never duplicated in apps)
- All SCSS tokens and utilities → `libs/styles` (never redefined at app level)
- All design decisions → Plectrum DS + Figma UI Kit
- All routes, utils, and services shared between apps → `libs/`
- If a token is missing from `libs/styles`, add it there **first**

### Rule — Storybook First
- Every component in `libs/ui` **must** have a `.stories.ts` file
- Develop and validate in Storybook **before** integrating into any app
- Cover all states: default, hover, disabled, loading, error, empty
- No component is "done" without a passing Storybook story

### Rule — PrimeNG First
- Always check PrimeNG before writing a custom component
- Extend or wrap PrimeNG components with BEMIT classes when restyling
- Never reimplement what PrimeNG already provides (tables, modals, dropdowns, etc.)

### Rule — Custom Components: Semantic & Minimal
When no PrimeNG equivalent exists:
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<nav>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<button>`, etc.)
- Apply ARIA roles and attributes for accessibility
- Keep it generic — no app-specific logic inside `libs/ui`
- Document the reason in the component's Storybook story

### Rule — No Direct Tailwind on HTML
Never apply utility classes directly in HTML templates. Always create a semantic BEM class.

```scss
// ✅ Correct — libs/styles/src/06-components/_card.scss
.c-card {
  @apply flex flex-col gap-4 p-6;

  &__header { @apply text-lg font-semibold; }
  &--highlighted { @apply border border-primary-500; }
}
```

```html
<!-- ✅ Correct -->
<div class="c-card c-card--highlighted">
  <div class="c-card__header">Title</div>
</div>

<!-- ❌ Wrong -->
<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 p-6 border border-primary-500">
```

### Rule — BEMIT Naming
| Type | Prefix | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Object (layout) | `o-` | `o-container`, `o-grid` |
| Component | `c-` | `c-card`, `c-button` |
| Utility | `u-` | `u-hidden`, `u-sr-only` |
| JS hook | `js-` | `js-modal-trigger` |
| State | `is-` / `has-` | `is-active`, `has-error` |

### Rule — No Dead Code
Remove unused functions, modules, commented-out code, and "kept for reference" logic.
Use git history instead of leaving dead code in the repo.

### Rule — Ask Questions Early
If a decision is ambiguous, requirements conflict, or something feels off:
- Create a question under `.ai/questions/` and surface it
- Never guess on major architectural decisions

### Rule — Before Starting Work
1. Read the project overview and current phase
2. Check recent logs and open questions
3. Ensure all tests pass before making changes
4. Only then begin implementation

---

## Component Checklist

Before marking any component complete:

- [ ] Built using PrimeNG where possible
- [ ] Styled with BEMIT classes in `libs/styles/src/06-components/`
- [ ] No Tailwind utility classes in HTML templates
- [ ] Storybook story created and covers all states
- [ ] No app-specific logic inside `libs/ui`
- [ ] Design tokens sourced from `libs/styles/src/01-settings/`
- [ ] Semantic HTML used throughout
- [ ] ARIA attributes applied where needed
- [ ] Exported from `libs/ui/src/index.ts`

---

## Component Naming Conventions

- **File**: `kebab-case` — `button.component.ts`, `data-table.component.ts`
- **Class**: `PascalCase` — `ButtonComponent`, `DataTableComponent`
- **Template BEM block**: `c-` prefixed kebab — `c-button`, `c-data-table`
- Elements: `c-button__icon`, `c-card__title`
- Modifiers: `c-button--primary`, `c-card--featured`
- Never use app-specific prefixes inside `libs/ui`
